LabourCropPyomo module¶

author: young

LabourCropPyomo.crplab_precalcs(params, r_vals)¶

Call crop labour precalc functions.

Parameters

  • params – dictionary which stores all arrays used to populate pyomo parameters.

  • report – dictionary which stores all report values.

LabourCropPyomo.labcrppyomo_local(params)¶

Builds pyomo variables, parameters and constraints

LabourCropPyomo.mach_labour_anyone(model, p)¶

Calculate the total labour required by anyone for fertilising, spraying, seeding, harvest, preperation, packing and monitoring.

Used in global constraint (con_labour_anyone). See CorePyomo

LabourCropPyomo.mach_labour_perm(model, p)¶

Calculate the total labour required by permanent staff for fertilising, spraying, seeding, harvest, preperation, packing and monitoring.

Used in global constraint (con_labour_perm). See CorePyomo
